This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of estimating the 6D pose of objects using only RGB images. It also proposes a novel method that uses an auto-encoder architecture to estimate the 3D coordinates of each object pixel without textured models. 

It could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as the problem of object pose estimation is relevant to robotics applications. 

The paper also proposes a novel loss function, which could be of interest to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper deals with the problem of handling symmetric objects, which could be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
